% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/ci_drift_heal.py` — standalone CI script with `if __name__ == '__main__'` entry point
- Example: `context/ci_drift_heal_example.py` — a provider-free execution
  contract for the public entry point. The example MUST build a single valid,
  fingerprinted module inside a disposable temporary project and call
  `main(..., dry_run=True)` only for that bounded fixture. It MUST use a
  minimal environment allowlist for the child, with no inherited provider credentials,
  PDD/Git configuration, proxy settings, Python paths, or cloud configuration.
  Replace ambient config locations with an isolated temporary HOME plus isolated
  XDG, AWS, Azure, and gcloud config paths inside the disposable project. Enforce
  a bounded timeout and set `sys.dont_write_bytecode = True` before any PDD import
  as well as `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1` in the child. It must not write to the source checkout or
  the caller's repository. It must never call `commit_and_push`, `heal_module`,
  or any non-dry-run healing path; it must never commit or push. If the main
  dry-run returns non-zero, the example MUST print a failure message and
  propagate that exact non-zero exit code; it MUST NOT print a success message. It may
  print `ci_drift_heal example completed successfully` only after a zero return.
  Regeneration tests MUST resolve direct imports, imported symbol aliases, and
  module-qualified aliases such as `import pdd.ci_drift_heal as drift`; reject
  forbidden `ast.Name` and `ast.Attribute` calls, and require every resolved
  `main` call to contain the literal keyword `dry_run=True`. A Git shim MUST
  parse Git global options (including `-C`, `-c`, `--git-dir`, `--work-tree`,
  their assignment forms, and `--`) before rejecting every write-capable
  subcommand. Tests MUST preserve and compare caller, source-checkout, and
  disposable workspace Git state, including HEAD, refs, config, and all `.git`
  administrative files. Source-checkout proof MUST be linked-worktree aware:
  hash the `.git` linked-worktree pointer, resolve both `git rev-parse --git-dir`
  and `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`, and compare the applicable
  admin/index/packed-refs/log state from the resolved worktree and common Git
  directories. A clean porcelain status alone is never sufficient. Keep imports
  lint-clean and terminate the file with a newline.
